line_1: But yet, a while he safely treads,
line_2: Nor yet ambition's glare misleads,

line_1: Resolv'd the darkling Dome he treads,
line_2: With weary Steps he quits the Shades,

line_1: Where rosy Health delighted treads!
line_2: Low murmuring, bow your verdant heads!

line_1: There as thy lightsome foot thus treads
line_2: Thy hand the dews so neatly threads

line_1: Where the sharp rock the Chamois treads,
line_2: Or where the whitening Snow-bird spreads

line_1: Yet cheer my paths if virtue treads,
line_2: Shine thro' the tear that sorrow sheds,

line_1: REAS'NING at every step he treads,
line_2: While meaner things whom instinct leads

line_1: Through pathless wilds she treads,
line_2: Its baneful berries spreads.

line_1: Play round her graceful footsteps, as she treads;
line_2: Pleased GNOMES, ascending from their earthy beds,

line_1: To fatal ills, that though the path he treads
line_2: Tell him he wanders, that his error leads

line_1: With strange deformity PLANTAGO treads,
line_2: A Monster-birth! and lifts his hundred heads;

line_1: Queen of the marsh, imperial DROSERA treads
line_2: Rush-fringed banks, and moss-embroider'd beds;

line_1: With measured step the Fairy Sovereign treads,
line_2: Shakes her high plume, and glitters o'er the meads;

line_1: Onward with loftier step the Beauty treads,
line_2: And trails the brinded ermine o'er the meads;

line_1: With some the path of glory treads,
line_2: And there collects his shining deeds;

line_1: In Paths uncertain, and unsafe he treads,
line_2: Who blindly follows other's fertile Heads.

line_1: For restless Proserpine for ever treads
line_2: In Paths unseen, o'er our devoted Heads;

line_1: Of Lands where Grass ne'r grows, or Mortal treads;
line_2: Legends of Fables fill our partial Heads,

line_1: Behind the steps that Misery treads,
line_2: Still, where rosy Pleasure leads,

line_1: Grass and flowers Quiet treads,
line_2: On the meads and mountain-heads,

line_1: Or Severn's flow'ry dales, where plenty treads,
line_2: Inglorious victory! Ye Cheshire meads,

line_1: And where no footstep treads.
line_2: In groves and flowery meads:

line_1: Or on Persian carpets treads,
line_2: When she trips along the meads,

line_1: The path her child obedient treads;
line_2: Then on with sullen step she leads,

line_1: I'm vex'd that like ourselves on earth he treads,
line_2: And scarce believe he hasn't got two heads.
